The paper presents a software framework for deep reinforcement learning research, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-fields such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer vision (cs.CV). The focus on reproducibility and benchmarking also suggests a strong connection to the machine learning and artificial intelligence communities. Therefore, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.RO, cs.SY, and cs.CV.
